:{{tx}}
:{{A|VO chapter2 12 yanqing 117.ogg}} '''Yanqing:''' Is this how you... "leave one side open"...? You let that borisin escape so you could track him.
:{{A|VO chapter2 12 feixiao 133.ogg}} '''Feixiao:''' This is the most common hunting tactic used by borisin.
:{{A|VO chapter2 12 feixiao 134.ogg}} '''Feixiao:''' I know the methods of these abominations all too well. They always leave an escape route for their prey, allowing them to flee in fear. Then they chase them like it's a game. Borisin get great satisfaction from the last struggles of their victims...
:{{A|VO chapter2 12 yanqing 118.ogg}} '''Yanqing:''' Have you witnessed these things firsthand? That guy called you a... war slave... What exactly have you experienced?
:{{A|VO chapter2 12 feixiao 135.ogg}} '''Feixiao:''' Well, just a hazy past that I can barely recollect. Long ago... I was one of them.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Wait, you're a borisin!?
::{{A|VO chapter2 12 feixiao 136.ogg}} '''Feixiao:''' The word "borisin" was only used to refer to those wolf masters. I'm a foxian who was born in one of the "fallen territories"...
::{{A|VO chapter2 12 feixiao 137.ogg}} '''Feixiao:''' In their eyes, we're mere consumables, cannon fodder used to slow down Xianzhou attacks on the battlefield.
::But you're a foxian, right?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} But you're a foxian, right?
:{{A|VO chapter2 12 feixiao 138.ogg}} '''Feixiao:''' Not all foxians are lucky enough to be born on a Xianzhou ship... I grew up in one of the worlds where borisin roam, known as the "fallen territories" by the people of the Yaoqing.
:{{A|VO chapter2 12 feixiao 139.ogg}} '''Feixiao:''' To the wolf masters, foxians are nothing but property, cannon fodder used to slow down the Xianzhou attacks on the battlefield.
:{{A|VO chapter2 12 yanqing 119.ogg}} '''Yanqing:''' But you... survived. And not only that, you became the general of the Yaoqing! If I get the chance, I'd love to hear stories of your past, General.
:{{tx}}
{{Dialogue End}}

